{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/work/eko-wave/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Eko Wave","date":"2017-04-01T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"April 1st, 2017","date_from_now":"3 years ago","last_modified_at":"2018-03-05T18:54:54.000Z","last_modified_at_from_now":"2 years ago","path":"/work/eko-wave/","author":null,"excerpt":"Site design and creative for Eko Wave — a team specializing in niche applications.","tags":["design","web development"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"aspectRatio":1.7741935483870968,"src":"/static/e4a9afde40422c447f2adbaea96ef41e/a2a79/eko-wave-feature.jpg","srcSet":"/static/e4a9afde40422c447f2adbaea96ef41e/6e883/eko-wave-feature.jpg 275w,\n/static/e4a9afde40422c447f2adbaea96ef41e/a09ef/eko-wave-feature.jpg 550w,\n/static/e4a9afde40422c447f2adbaea96ef41e/a2a79/eko-wave-feature.jpg 1024w","sizes":"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"},"fixed":{"src":"/static/e4a9afde40422c447f2adbaea96ef41e/a2a79/eko-wave-feature.jpg","height":576,"width":1024}}},"toc":null,"comments":false,"comments_locked":null,"hide_meta":true},"id":"310be993-2daa-57a6-8d85-669dc2808ec4","html":"<p><strong>Eko Wave LLC</strong> is a company started by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/endonend\">two</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/bjpmba\">pals</a> and myself to provide value to niche consumers through well-thought-out applications.</p>\n<p>When designing the logo I wanted something that played off of the word <em>wave</em> found in our name, while keeping with a color palette we established in Eko’s previous life.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 900px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 136.72727272727272%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"Eko Wave logo guide\"\n        title=\"Eko Wave logo guide\"\n        data-src=\"/static/ca04b53a03babf1b94ec1f793bbac6ab/062c0/eko-wave-logo-guide.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/ca04b53a03babf1b94ec1f793bbac6ab/16841/eko-wave-logo-guide.jpg 275w,\n/static/ca04b53a03babf1b94ec1f793bbac6ab/50c97/eko-wave-logo-guide.jpg 550w,\n/static/ca04b53a03babf1b94ec1f793bbac6ab/062c0/eko-wave-logo-guide.jpg 900w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>Taking things a step further I created a basic style tile<sup id=\"fnref-1\"><a href=\"#fn-1\" class=\"footnote-ref\">1</a></sup> document that helped me brainstorm how color, typography, and imagery fit and sell the concept to my partners. It would also serve as blueprint for me to design the site in browser — making for a more enjoyable and loose experience instead of being tied to a .PSD mockup I needed to CSSify<sup id=\"fnref-2\"><a href=\"#fn-2\" class=\"footnote-ref\">2</a></sup> exactly.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 780px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 220.00000000000003%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"Eko Wave style tile\"\n        title=\"Eko Wave style tile\"\n        data-src=\"/static/6b4aea732e0c8061e2940a293e33137e/90725/eko-wave-style-tile.jpg\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/6b4aea732e0c8061e2940a293e33137e/16841/eko-wave-style-tile.jpg 275w,\n/static/6b4aea732e0c8061e2940a293e33137e/50c97/eko-wave-style-tile.jpg 550w,\n/static/6b4aea732e0c8061e2940a293e33137e/90725/eko-wave-style-tile.jpg 780w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>The end result was a simple one page site that will ultimately grow as we build out our application and service portfolio.</p>\n<div class=\"footnotes\">\n<hr>\n<ol>\n<li id=\"fn-1\">\n<p>Style Tiles are a design deliverable consisting of fonts, colors and interface elements that communicate the essence of a visual brand for the web. (<a href=\"http://styletil.es/\">Learn more</a>)</p>\n<a href=\"#fnref-1\" class=\"footnote-backref\">↩</a>\n</li>\n<li id=\"fn-2\">\n<p>Is CSSify even a word?</p>\n<a href=\"#fnref-2\" class=\"footnote-backref\">↩</a>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</div>","excerpt":"Eko Wave LLC is a company started by two pals and myself to provide value to niche consumers through well-thought-out applications. When…","timeToRead":1,"tableOfContents":""},"comments":{"edges":[]}},"pageContext":{"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/work/relic-scout/","title":"Relic Scout","categories":["work"],"tags":["design","web development"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/28041/opensource/github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/work/relilc-scout.md"},"previous":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/work/jekyll-themes/","title":"Jekyll themes","categories":["work"],"tags":["Jekyll","web development","design","open source","GitHub"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/28041/opensource/github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/work/jekyll-themes.md"}}}}